evidence.source_document: Complaint for Declaratory and Injunctive Relief
evidence.text: Case 4:25-cv-00026-JTJ Document 1 Filed 04/04/25 Page 12 of 38 34. The War of 1812 created additional U.S. and Britain dispute borders. 35. On December 24, 1814 the Treaty of Ghent was signed, restoring pre-war boundaries and marking the end of British support for Native American Indians. On February 17, 1815 the U.S. Senate unanimously approved Treaty of Ghent.
